Conchatumadre is an insult in Spanish, commonly said to be of Peruvian origin among South Americans.

Most notable for having been called "Conchatumadre" as a boy is the nationally recognized peruvian depicted below, Diego Alonso Acosta Ruiz, now 22 years old.

